"{\"uid\": \"thenation.com-article-society-paris-olympics-dispatch-military-security\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  Forgot Your Password?\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 23, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"New toThe Nation?Subscribe  Print subscriber?Activateyour online access  In the last year, an estimated 12,500 vulnerable Paris residents were forced from their homes.\", \"from\": 25, \"to\": 192, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 147, \"end\": 152, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8791075137729838e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French soldiers stand guard near to Eiffel Tower in Paris on July 21 ahead of the Paris 2024 Olympic and Paralympic Games.\", \"from\": 194, \"to\": 316, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 194, \"end\": 200, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9731020808717722, \"rank\": 0.024830221659780435, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 246, \"end\": 251, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8791075137729838e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 299, \"end\": 315, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999997066825447, \"rank\": 2.895116142321051e-07, \"text\": \"Paralympic Games\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris-The contradictions of the 2024 Paris Summer Olympics are clear as soon as one steps off the plane.\", \"from\": 318, \"to\": 422, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Corporate sponsors blare cheery ads for the Olympic Games while the French military-armed with weapons more at home in a war zone or bombastic action flick-patrol the grounds.\", \"from\": 423, \"to\": 598, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There are 50,000 police and military in the streets aided by AI-powered video surveillance technology, which the French National Assemblylegalizedin 2023 with theOlympic Games Law.\", \"from\": 599, \"to\": 779, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On day one, we were accosted by a soldier for filming a sign informing people that they could not proceed past a metal gate to see the Seine River, where the opening ceremony is to be staged.\", \"from\": 780, \"to\": 971, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is Olympic Paris.\", \"from\": 972, \"to\": 994, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 988, \"end\": 993, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8791075137729838e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You can not go to the Seine, but you can have your personal information taken down for publicizing this fact.\", \"from\": 995, \"to\": 1104, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1017, \"end\": 1022, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0942299594147434e-13, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French are not passively imbibing the Olympic spectacle.\", \"from\": 1106, \"to\": 1166, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1110, \"end\": 1116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9731020808717722, \"rank\": 0.024830221659780435, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tomorrow activists aremobilizingin Place de la R\\u00e9publique to challenge the five-ring juggernaut that has rolled into their city, with groups likeSaccage 2024,Le Revers de La M\\u00e9daille, andExtinction Rebellionout front.\", \"from\": 1167, \"to\": 1384, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1202, \"end\": 1224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_R\\u00e9publique\", \"score\": 0.9919463876317131, \"rank\": 0.007170795306387261, \"text\": \"Place de la R\\u00e9publique\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_R\\u00e9publique\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_R\\u00e9publique\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The \\\"counter-opening ceremony\\\" promises to raise numerous criticisms of the Olympics, from the displacement of migrants and unhoused people to the fake environmentalism embedded in France's Olympic messaging.\", \"from\": 1385, \"to\": 1593, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1566, \"end\": 1572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9252580890522655, \"rank\": 0.08077164847943842, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paul Alauzy, an organizer with Le Revers de La M\\u00e9daille andM\\u00e9decins du Monde, explained to us the philosophy undergirding the mass displacement of poor people that unfolded in the weeks and years before the Paris Olympics: \\\"In Paris, the social cleansing can be understood with a double logic of dispersion: a dispersion within the Olympic's city public space, to avoid tent cities, slums, squats, and disperse the marginalized people, and a dispersion within the whole country, so that to delocalize the unwanted and push the misery away from the Olympic city.\\\"\", \"from\": 1595, \"to\": 2157, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1629, \"end\": 1635, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Revers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Revers\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Revers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Revers\"}, {\"begin\": 1822, \"end\": 1827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8791075137729838e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Aresearch studyfrom Le Revers de La M\\u00e9daille found that over the past year, some 12,500 vulnerable people were forcibly removed from their homes.\", \"from\": 2158, \"to\": 2303, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2181, \"end\": 2187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Revers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Revers\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Revers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Revers\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French Olympic Committee made a big show of banning the hijab for French Muslim women athletes.\", \"from\": 2305, \"to\": 2404, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2309, \"end\": 2333, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_National_Olympic_and_Sports_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_National_Olympic_and_Sports_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_National_Olympic_and_Sports_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 2375, \"end\": 2381, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9731020808717722, \"rank\": 0.024830221659780435, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2382, \"end\": 2388, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\", \"score\": 0.9999415718965368, \"rank\": 5.843143068765988e-05, \"text\": \"Muslim\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the sports journalist Shireen Ahmed from the CBC said to us, \\\"The hijab ban in France not only goes against the Olympic Charter, it speaks boldly about the hypocrisy that we have come to expect from the IOC.\", \"from\": 2405, \"to\": 2615, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2430, \"end\": 2443, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shireen_Ahmed\", \"score\": 0.9999999838792065, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shireen Ahmed\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shireen_Ahmed\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shireen_Ahmed\"}, {\"begin\": 2453, \"end\": 2456, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBC_News\", \"score\": 0.999903117166011, \"rank\": 9.689222060175445e-05, \"text\": \"CBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBC_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBC_News\"}, {\"begin\": 2487, \"end\": 2493, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9252580890522655, \"rank\": 0.08077164847943842, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}, {\"begin\": 2611, \"end\": 2614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.252641133344062e-31, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Excluding Black and brown women from sport is not only heartbreaking, it kills any opportunity for social inclusion from a specific community.\", \"from\": 2616, \"to\": 2758, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This experience shatters confidence in sport from young girls who know that if they are forced to choose between faith and sport, they might lose something so precious to them.\", \"from\": 2759, \"to\": 2935, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's isolating and hurtful.\", \"from\": 2936, \"to\": 2963, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is also unjust.\\\"\", \"from\": 2964, \"to\": 2983, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here in France, people are not exactly thrilled to be hosting the Olympics.One pollfound that as the Paris Games approach, more than 65 percent of the population are either indifferent (36 percent), concerned (24 percent), or angry (5 percent).\", \"from\": 2985, \"to\": 3229, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2993, \"end\": 2999, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9252580890522655, \"rank\": 0.08077164847943842, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After Paris authorities originally promised free metro tickets during the Olympics, riding feesnearly doubledfrom \\u20ac2.15 to \\u20ac4.\", \"from\": 3230, \"to\": 3356, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3236, \"end\": 3241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8791075137729838e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Beloved public spaces like the famed Pompidou Centre are now clogged up with tawdry sports commercialism, with Nike ads blazing on the building's storied facade like a Las Vegas casino.\", \"from\": 3357, \"to\": 3542, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3468, \"end\": 3472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/MIM-3_Nike_Ajax\", \"score\": 0.9836995785899451, \"rank\": 0.01657052799930212, \"text\": \"Nike\", \"types\": [\"Q728\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/MIM-3_Nike_Ajax\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/MIM-3_Nike_Ajax\"}, {\"begin\": 3525, \"end\": 3534, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Las_Vegas_Strip\", \"score\": 0.9976861374977712, \"rank\": 0.0023192288748676406, \"text\": \"Las Vegas\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Las_Vegas_Strip\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Las_Vegas_Strip\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Upon seeing this, one social media user, in a paroxysm of extreme Frenchness,posted\\\"I have no words in the face of such horror.\\\"\", \"from\": 3543, \"to\": 3671, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But the unions of Paris have not rolled over.\", \"from\": 3673, \"to\": 3718, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3691, \"end\": 3696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8791075137729838e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the Games approached, worker power has leveraged the once-in-a-generation opportunity to score wage hikes.\", \"from\": 3719, \"to\": 3828, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Garbage collectors, train drivers, air-traffic controllers, and police are using their leverage to demand Olympic bonuses.\", \"from\": 3829, \"to\": 3951, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Now, with the opening ceremony slated for Friday, the SFA-CGT union representing around 10 percent of the dancers in the kick-off eventfileda strike notice over \\\"outrageous disparities\\\" in pay between performers.\", \"from\": 3952, \"to\": 4164, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The political issues on display are not limited merely to the Parisian.\", \"from\": 4166, \"to\": 4237, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Justice for Palestine and anger at the inclusion of Israeli Olympians, which we will surely write more upon in the days ahead, is very much on display.\", \"from\": 4238, \"to\": 4389, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4250, \"end\": 4259, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\", \"score\": 0.9996891921703053, \"rank\": 0.0003109041146979447, \"text\": \"Palestine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\"}, {\"begin\": 4290, \"end\": 4297, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 0.9995252926747237, \"rank\": 0.0004749310120736559, \"text\": \"Israeli\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There have been demonstrations to this effect and protesters have promised to protestinsideOlympic venues.\", \"from\": 4390, \"to\": 4496, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What angers protesters is the hypocrisy of sanctioning the Russian Olympic team for the invasion of Ukraine while not only ignoring but defending Israel in the face of international condemnation over their genocidal war on the people of Gaza.\", \"from\": 4497, \"to\": 4739, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4556, \"end\": 4576, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_Olympic_Committee_athletes_at_the_2022_Winter_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6618175859467098e-23, \"text\": \"Russian Olympic team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_Olympic_Committee_athletes_at_the_2022_Winter_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_Olympic_Committee_athletes_at_the_2022_Winter_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 4597, \"end\": 4604, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9999999960809873, \"rank\": 3.919134201524761e-09, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 4643, \"end\": 4649, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4023317957747496e-17, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}, {\"begin\": 4734, \"end\": 4738, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"score\": 0.9999669101834667, \"rank\": 3.3090911197898015e-05, \"text\": \"Gaza\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All of this has created a volatile scene at what is probably the most politically charged Olympics since Mexico City in 1968 when John Carlos and Tommie Smith raised their fists to the heavens.\", \"from\": 4741, \"to\": 4934, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4846, \"end\": 4857, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico_City\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.9900484106298094e-17, \"text\": \"Mexico City\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico_City\"}, {\"begin\": 4871, \"end\": 4882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Carlos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"John Carlos\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Carlos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Carlos\"}, {\"begin\": 4887, \"end\": 4899, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommie_Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tommie Smith\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommie_Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommie_Smith\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What we are seeing in the City of Light are certainly Parisian problems and the impacts of larger geopolitical strife.\", \"from\": 4935, \"to\": 5053, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But they are also at their coreOlympicproblems that transcend Paris, that have been imported into the city when its leaders chose to bid on the Olympics nearly 10 years ago.\", \"from\": 5054, \"to\": 5227, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5116, \"end\": 5121, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8791075137729838e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For many here, the Olympics were a distant dream hovering in the future.\", \"from\": 5228, \"to\": 5300, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Well, now things are getting real.\", \"from\": 5301, \"to\": 5335, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And French soldiers are posted around the city to remind you of this almost surreal reality.\", \"from\": 5336, \"to\": 5428, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5340, \"end\": 5346, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9731020808717722, \"rank\": 0.024830221659780435, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We will be in Paris to follow the off-the-field machinations forThe Nation, so stay tuned.\", \"from\": 5429, \"to\": 5519, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5443, \"end\": 5448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8791075137729838e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A big thank you to Garry Whannel for letting us use his flat asThe Nation's Paris headquarters for the 2024 Olympics.\", \"from\": 5521, \"to\": 5638, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5597, \"end\": 5602, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8791075137729838e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even before February 28, the reasons for Donald Trump's imploding approval rating were abundantly clear: untrammeled corruption and personal enrichment to the tune of billions of dollars during an affordability crisis, a foreign policy guided only by his own derelict sense of morality, and the deployment of a murderous campaign of occupation, detention, and deportation on American streets.\", \"from\": 5640, \"to\": 6032, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5681, \"end\": 5693, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999999984383976, \"rank\": 1.5612987843303837e-09, \"text\": \"Donald Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}, {\"begin\": 6015, \"end\": 6023, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.087173565427562e-16, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now an undeclared, unauthorized, unpopular, and unconstitutional war of aggression against Iran has spread like wildfire through the region and into Europe.\", \"from\": 6034, \"to\": 6190, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6125, \"end\": 6129, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"score\": 0.9999986507309594, \"rank\": 7.272872723632278e-07, \"text\": \"Iran\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A new \\\"forever war\\\"-with an ever-increasing likelihood of American troops on the ground-may very well be upon us.\", \"from\": 6191, \"to\": 6304, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6249, \"end\": 6257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.087173565427562e-16, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As we have seen over and over, this administration uses lies, misdirection, and attempts to flood the zone to justify its abuses of power at home and abroad.\", \"from\": 6306, \"to\": 6463, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Just as Trump, Marco Rubio, and Pete Hegseth offer erratic and contradictory rationales for the attacks on Iran, the administration is also spreading the lie that the upcoming midterm elections are under threat from noncitizens on voter rolls.\", \"from\": 6464, \"to\": 6707, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6472, \"end\": 6477, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999998911043863, \"rank\": 1.0889587163458171e-07, \"text\": \"Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}, {\"begin\": 6479, \"end\": 6490, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marco_Rubio\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.1274863014212923e-35, \"text\": \"Marco Rubio\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marco_Rubio\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marco_Rubio\"}, {\"begin\": 6496, \"end\": 6508, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pete_Hegseth\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pete Hegseth\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pete_Hegseth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pete_Hegseth\"}, {\"begin\": 6571, \"end\": 6575, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"score\": 0.9999986507309594, \"rank\": 7.272872723632278e-07, \"text\": \"Iran\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When these lies go unchecked, they become the basis for further authoritarian encroachment and war.\", \"from\": 6708, \"to\": 6807, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In these dark times, independent journalism is uniquely able to uncover the falsehoods that threaten our republic-and civilians around the world-and shine a bright light on the truth.\", \"from\": 6809, \"to\": 6992, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Nation's experienced team of writers, editors, and fact-checkers understands the scale of what we are up against and the urgency with which we have to act.\", \"from\": 6994, \"to\": 7153, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's why we are publishing critical reporting and analysis of the war on Iran, ICE violence at home, new forms of voter suppression emerging in the courts, and much more.\", \"from\": 7154, \"to\": 7326, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7229, \"end\": 7233, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"score\": 0.9999986507309594, \"rank\": 7.272872723632278e-07, \"text\": \"Iran\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But this journalism is possible only with your support.\", \"from\": 7328, \"to\": 7383, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This March,The Nationneeds to raise $50,000 to ensure that we have the resources for reporting and analysis that sets the record straight and empowers people of conscience to organize.Will you donate today?\", \"from\": 7385, \"to\": 7591, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dave Zirin is the sports editor atThe Nation.\", \"from\": 7593, \"to\": 7638, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7593, \"end\": 7603, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dave_Zirin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dave Zirin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dave_Zirin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dave_Zirin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is the author of 11 books on the politics of sports.\", \"from\": 7639, \"to\": 7694, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He is also the coproducer and writer of the new documentaryBehind the Shield: The Power and Politics of the NFL.\", \"from\": 7695, \"to\": 7807, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7803, \"end\": 7806, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Football_League\", \"score\": 0.9999999139527099, \"rank\": 8.221304756190479e-08, \"text\": \"NFL\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Football_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Football_League\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jules Boykoff is a professor of political science at Pacific University in Oregon and the author of six books on the Olympic Games, most recentlyWhat Are the Olympics For?\", \"from\": 7809, \"to\": 7980, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7809, \"end\": 7822, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jules_Boykoff\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jules Boykoff\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jules_Boykoff\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jules_Boykoff\"}, {\"begin\": 7862, \"end\": 7880, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pacific_University\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pacific University\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pacific_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pacific_University\"}, {\"begin\": 7884, \"end\": 7890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oregon\", \"score\": 0.9999999964875315, \"rank\": 3.512300368012814e-09, \"text\": \"Oregon\", \"types\": [\"Q